On Thu, Apr 15, 2010 at 2:07 PM, Kerry McGinn <ajmcginn(-at-)comcast.net> wrote:

> This likely has no relevance to this dialogue, but I can tell you
> first-hand that a blown piston will cause blue smoke to gush out the back
> and also splatter specks of oil all over the rear hatches and bumper.  This
> happened more than once to me due to an overheating No. 3 cylinder (the
> classic weak spot in the air-cooled engine).  The pistons in each case had a
> small hole burned in the top surface, smaller than you might imagine. Thus
> the oil spewing out the exhaust valve and all over the back. At the other
> extreme, a spark-plug wire jiggling off the plug can just as readily reduce
> your bus to a gasping 3-cylinder cripple.
>
